i’ve been feeling intimidated about writing something that’ll be worthy of this day. i feel like i probably wrote better words for some random anniversary or your birthday or even valentines day; maybe i’m just psyching myself out. i should already know that no matter what i write it’ll be enough. for 10 years even at my absolute lowest, my absolute worst i’ve always been enough. thank you for loving me for 10 years; we’ve both grown so much and yet we’re still the exact same people we were in your room looking at your CDs so long ago, we’ve overcome so much, and i know nothing could have prepared us for how hard the last year has been but just like we always do, we made it. we made it to where we’ve always wanted to be. you are my best friend, the coolest, funniest most talented & handsome guy i’ve ever known & the very best dad. every day it hits me how lucky i am and i still don’t know how i did it. i know i don’t always show it, but i am so deeply thankful that somehow, we both ended up somewhere we thought for sure we didn’t belong & found each other. we’ve seen the hardest, darkest lows, especially lately, so surely that means things can only get better. I know they can only get better. I’m so proud of the person I’ve been lucky enough to have a front row seat watching you become. No matter how hard it got, it’s always been you. It’ll always be you. Happy 10 year anniversary @mattmezzatesta 🖤

we adopted a bunny! meet the newest member of our family, rootbeer 💕 he’s a one-year old netherland dwarf & you might not have caught it (it’s hardly noticeable) but he’s actually a little lopsided🥴 rootie has a permanent head tilt caused by the parasite e. cuniculi that attacks the brain & can cause neurological issues in serious cases. his tilt doesn’t impact him very much at all now other than some occasional excited rolling, but otherwise he’s a normal, happy guy who has figured out his own way of doing things thanks to the love & care of the amazing @georgiahrs that rescued him as a baby & have done so much to help him become the healthy, strong boy he is now. we are just obsessed with him in a way that’s hard to put into words; i’ve been moved to tears like twice just staring at him and being struck by how adorable he is. his cuddly, loving nature also reminds me a lot of my childhood best friend, frosty the holland lop, and i’m so glad to have another bunny in my life after all these years. i’m even more glad that bunny is rootbeer, the most wonderful, beautiful bunny in the whole wide world. #headtilthopper #headtiltbunny #disabledrabbits

my sweet crooked Rootie 💕 i’m so grateful we found each other; he’s a strong, brave little bunny with a big personality & he brings us so much joy. his situation & care is complex but it’s all just Rootbeer stuff; his normal & our new normal that comes with the privilege of being his family.

if you’re curious here’s the rootie deets:

Rootbeer’s head tilt is permanent, caused by the parasite e. Cuniculi. Rabbits with EC have it for life. It’s pretty common but most never show symptoms. If it does “flare up” it can attack the brain & cause neurological issues like dizziness & a head tilt, which can resolve over time with treatment. Sometimes though (especially if not treated ASAP) the damage is permanent.

Rootie was the runt (making him immunocompromised to begin with) & his EC initially flared up when he was a baby & wasn’t treated right away. Despite that he has a great quality of life. He’s able to hop, explore, climb, play, cuddle, groom himself, & be a bunny. There are some things he can't do but he's still SO young (1 year & 4 months) and has plenty of time to learn & adapt. He does face some challenges that we help him cope with, like dizzy spells. He isn’t always dizzy but when he is he feels the need to roll if he turns a certain way, sending him flailing feet over head & hay flying everywhere. It’s really heartbreaking to watch but thankfully there are meds we keep on hand that help a lot whenever he needs them. We also have to watch out for EC flare ups that can be triggered by stress; in fact we are treating him now after the adjustment of moving to a new home caused a potential flare up, but he’s doing great so far & settling in well. 

There isn’t much info out there on EC so we’re learning as we go but thanks to the guidance of the rescue we adopted him from, his wonderful veterinary team & the amazing resources that I'm SO thankful to have found from @tiltedbunco theres so much hope for head-tilt bunnies & a lot we can do to help them live full lives. And he's got himself; his own indomitable little spirit that fought to be here & wants to be here. Boy are we happy that he is 💕

#disabledbunny #headtiltbunny #disabledrabbit #headtiltrabbit
